 of finite energy resources; and, given the country's complex electoral government and global political position, the obstacles toward effecting policy reform. Sustaining India's Growth Miracle is a valuable resource for practitioners, policymakers, students, and scholars. It tackles issues from political, economic, and academic perspectives, and the concluding chapter, a talk given by the commerce and industry minister of India, discusses the country's position as a world power, outlining several reasons for its success and exploring the difficulties that lie ahead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aUnited States - Relations - India. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh1 aArora, Ashish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhagwati, Jagdish N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhagwati, Jagdish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhagwati, Jagdish, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBosworth, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalomiris, Charles W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalomiris, Charles, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDesai, Mihir A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGovinda Rao, M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevy, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNath, Kamal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPanagariya, Arvind, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSen, Ronen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShourie, Arun, econtributor.4ctb4htt